  "id": "019d2e1d-cfc3-72b3-a050-3a3ed2a101df",
  "content": "# Decay Mathematics — Decisions (March 2026)\n\n## Decay Function: Power-Law\n`D(t) = (1 + t_days)^(-α)` where t = days since creation (not last access).\nFat tail ensures Cold entries retain nonzero scores for reversible promotion.\n\n## Alpha Values (per memory type)\nStructural=0, Procedural=0.10, Decisional=0.15, Analytical=0.30, Episodic=0.60\n\n## Composite Retention Score: Additive\n```\nretention_score = 0.35 × D(t, α_type) \n               + 0.30 × A(access_count, days_since_access)\n               + 0.20 × G(inbound_edge_count)\n               + 0.15 × C(confidence)\n```\n\n### Component definitions\n- D(t) = (1+t)^(-α) — power-law, creation time, range [0,1]\n- A = (log(1+count)/log(1+100)) × (1+days_since_access)^(-0.3) — range [0,1]\n- G = min(inbound_edges / 10, 1.0) — inbound only, range [0,1]\n- C = confidence if set, else 0.7 default — range [0,1]\n\n### Key properties\n- Additive, not multiplicative: access/graph can rescue old entries from decay\n- New entries start Warm (~0.45-0.50), must earn Hot through access or connections\n- Session affinity boosts are retrieval-layer, not tier-layer\n- Weights: decay 35%, access 30%, graph 20%, confidence 15%\n\n## Tier Thresholds (with hysteresis)\n- Demotion: Hot→Warm < 0.50, Warm→Cold < 0.25, Cold→Forgotten < 0.05\n- Promotion: Cold→Warm >= 0.35, Warm→Hot >= 0.60\n- Gap of 0.10 prevents oscillation",
